\pard\f0\fs28  (ix) Apex of rhizome usually with long hairs. Plant with long, simple eglandular and sometimes subplumose hairs throughout. Basal leaves numerous; cauline 1-4, more or less amplexicaul. Capitula 1-2, on long peduncles. Ligules with numerous, short simple eglandular or glandular hairs at apex. Stigmas yellow. Achenes 3·5-4 mm, dark. Margins of receptacular pits dentate, slightly ciliate.
