\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 125. H. mixtum} group ({\i H. phlomoides} / {\i piliferum}). Plant with dense, long subplumose hairs and simple eglandular hairs throughout. Stems (5-)10-20 cm. Basal leaves 10-40 × 7-25 mm, ovate, elliptical or obovate, obtuse to subacute, undulate, entire to denticulate, narrowed into a winged petiole; cauline 1-4, the lower like the basal but sessile and more or less amplexicaul, the upper usually bract-like. Capitula 1-2; peduncles long, with numerous stellate hairs and few small glandular hairs. Involucre 10-12 × 10-13 mm; bracts acute, with a few small glandular hairs amongst the long simple eglandular and subplumose hairs. Ligules with dense, small glandular hairs at apex. 1700-2500{\i  m. • Pyrenees, Cordillera Cantábrica.} Ga Hs.
